Current status: navigating how to exist on this app as a mom lol

It’s no secret that I haven’t posted much on this page since we welcomed our tiny human into our world. I’ve been trying to figure out how to go about existing in this space without making this page all about her even though my entire world right now is all about her. I want to keep this space for me, and she may make an appearance here and there, but just as I was able to choose how I exist on the internet, I want to let her have the same choice later on. So for those of you who were worried that this was going to turn into a baby page, don’t worry (or do lol), you’re stuck with me!

That being said, my tall style page @tallestmermaid is going to include some lifestyle, mama and baby content as I navigate motherhood, so for my fellow mamas (even if you’re not tall), that’s where you can find me 💖

📷 @nathancyprys

The very first time I got pregnant I felt like my brain chemistry was permanently altered so I knew that when I actually became a mom it would change everything. And it has. We’re about halfway through year one and it’s hard. And beautiful. And the more I get to know this little human I made, the more I accept this new self I’m becoming. It’s pretty freaking cool.
•
